INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '2d6edc2b-5c83-48f7-badf-ecb4e4370871',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$wagmi v2 — Built on viem, Not ethers$escape$,
  $escape$wagmi v2 dropped ethers.js entirely and rebuilt its internals on viem. This isn't just a dependency swap — it changes how you interact with low-level primitives throughout your app.

Every wagmi hook now returns viem-native types. `useBalance` returns a `bigint` balance, not an ethers `BigNumber`. `useReadContract` expects viem's `Abi` type for the `abi` param. Error types are viem's `ContractFunctionRevertedError`, `UserRejectedRequestError`, etc. — structured, typed, and narrowable without string matching.

The `config` object you pass to `WagmiProvider` accepts a `client` built with viem's `createPublicClient` and `createWalletClient` under the hood via `createConfig`. You can extract those clients directly with `getPublicClient(config)` and `getWalletClient(config)` for raw viem calls outside React.

This matters because you can now mix wagmi hooks with direct viem calls sharing the same transport and chain config — no duplicate RPC connections, no type impedance mismatch between layers. Passing ABIs as `const` assertions gives you fully inferred return types end-to-end, from contract ABI to your component's JSX.$escape$,
  $escape$import { createConfig, http, getPublicClient } from 'wagmi'
import { mainnet } from 'wagmi/chains'
import { createPublicClient } from 'viem'

const config = createConfig({
  chains: [mainnet],
  transports: { [mainnet.id]: http() },
})

// Extract the underlying viem client — same transport, no extra RPC
const client = getPublicClient(config, { chainId: mainnet.id })

const block = await client.getBlockNumber()
const balance = await client.getBalance({ address: '0xd8dA6BF26964aF9D7eEd9e03E53415D37aA96045' })

console.log(block, balance) // bigint, bigint — viem-native, no BigNumber wrapper$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
